# PHONE UPLOAD GUIDE — one file at a time, no zip needed

Your repo already has these folders (from the original scaffold), so you're
replacing files, not creating folders.

## How to upload each file on your phone

1. In your browser, open the repo and tap into the folder listed below.
2. Tap **Add file → Upload files**.
3. Choose the file from your phone's Downloads.
4. Tap **Commit changes**. GitHub replaces the old file automatically when
   the name matches.

Tip: request the desktop site in your mobile browser if the Add file button
is hidden (Safari: AA icon → Request Desktop Website; Chrome: ⋮ → Desktop site).

