If a folder is missing (e.g. lib/data/), use **Add file → Create new file**
instead, type the path including the folder — for example
`lib/data/app_database.dart` — then paste the file's contents and commit.
Typing a `/` in the name box creates the folder.

## After all 16 are up

- Delete any leftover old files in lib/ that mention shared_preferences
  (open the file → trash-can icon → commit).
- One step still needs a computer: generating `lib/data/app_database.g.dart`
  (SETUP.md step 4 — a single command). The app won't build without it, but
  uploading everything else from your phone now is perfectly fine; run that
  command whenever you're next at a computer.
